# 🎯 DOM with CSS

JavaScript can change CSS properties dynamically using the DOM.

### HTML

```html
<h1 id="heading">Hello Akshita</h1>

<button onclick="changeColor()">Change Color</button>
```

### JavaScript

```javascript
function changeColor(){

document.getElementById("heading").style.color="red";

document.getElementById("heading").style.fontSize="45px";

document.getElementById("heading").style.backgroundColor="yellow";

}
```

---

# 🏗 Creating an Element using DOM

The `createElement()` method is used to create a new HTML element dynamically.

### JavaScript

```javascript
let heading=document.createElement("h2");

heading.innerHTML="Welcome to JavaScript";

document.body.appendChild(heading);
```

---

# 📥 insertAdjacentHTML()

The `insertAdjacentHTML()` method inserts HTML at four different positions relative to an existing element.

### HTML

```html
<div id="box">

<h2>JavaScript DOM</h2>

</div>
```

---

## 1. beforebegin

```javascript
let box=document.getElementById("box");

box.insertAdjacentHTML("beforebegin","<p>Before Begin</p>");
```

---

## 2. afterbegin

```javascript
box.insertAdjacentHTML("afterbegin","<p>After Begin</p>");
```

---

## 3. beforeend

```javascript
box.insertAdjacentHTML("beforeend","<p>Before End</p>");
```

---

## 4. afterend

```javascript
box.insertAdjacentHTML("afterend","<p>After End</p>");
```

